	<h1>Careers</h1>
	<p>
		At Tactical Cyber, we believe strong security starts with a strong team. Our work is challenging, practical, and grounded in real-world problem solving, but we are equally committed to maintaining a healthy work-life balance. We offer competitive compensation and benefits, including health coverage, retirement options, and generous paid time off. Team members are supported in their professional growth through tuition reimbursement, certification support, and ongoing training opportunities. Whether working independently or collaborating across engagements, our culture emphasizes discipline, curiosity, and steady, sustainable performance.</p>
	<hr>
	<div style="padding: 15px; background-color: #f0f8ff; margin-bottom: 25px;">
	<h1>Current Openings</h1>
	<details>
	<summary style="cursor: zoom-in;"><strong>Penetration Tester</strong></summary>
	<p>Daniel Mercer founded Tactical Cyber after more than a decade working in IT operations and cybersecurity roles across both public and private sectors. His early career focused on network administration and infrastructure support, where he developed a strong appreciation for the operational realities that many security programs overlook.</p>
	<p>Over time, Mercer transitioned into security engineering and incident response, supporting organizations through ransomware events and large-scale system disruptions. These experiences shaped his belief that effective cybersecurity must be grounded in disciplined IT operations.</p>
	<p>As CEO, he continues to guide the company’s strategic direction, emphasizing sustainable security practices, client transparency, and long-term risk reduction.</p>
	</details>
	<p><strong>Tactical Cyber LLC<strong>
Remote / Hybrid (U.S.-based preferred)</p>
    <p><strong>Position Overview</strong>
    Tactical Cyber is seeking a skilled and motivated Penetration Tester to join our growing cybersecurity team. In this role, you will conduct authorized, controlled security assessments that simulate real-world attacks against client environments.

You will identify vulnerabilities across networks, systems, and applications, validate their impact through exploitation, and provide clear, actionable reporting to support remediation efforts. This position blends technical execution with client-facing communication, supporting organizations that rely on Tactical Cyber for defensible, practical security outcomes.

Penetration testers play a proactive role in cybersecurity by simulating attacks to uncover weaknesses before adversaries can exploit them.<p>
